HEADWORD: Rheotome
<hw>Rhe"o*tome</hw> <pr>(r⟦emac⟧"⟦osl⟧*t⟦omac⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>"rei^n</grk> to flow + <grk>te`mnein</grk> to cut.]</ety>
<fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>An instrument which periodically or otherwise
interrupts an electric current.</def> <rj><au>Wheatstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
